## ðŸ§© Scripts and Repositories (Scripts)
Practical OSS tools and script collections for automating OSINT tasks.

- [datasploit](https://github.com/datasploit/datasploit) â€” a collection of modules for collecting data on objects (people, domain, IP).
- [ReconDog](https://github.com/s0md3v/ReconDog) â€” a multi-purpose reconnaissance utility (supports multiple modules).
- [solana-mev-bot](https://github.com/i3visio/solana-mev-bot) â€” an example bot/script for blockchain analytics (Solana).
- [LHF](https://github.com/blindfuzzy/LHF) â€” a repository with tools/scripts (various tasks).
- [sherlock](https://github.com/sherlock-project/sherlock) â€” profile search by nicknames on dozens of platforms.
- [AutOSINT](https://github.com/bharshbarger/AutOSINT) â€” automation of basic OSINT tasks.
- [snoop](https://github.com/snooppr/snoop) â€” scripts for analyzing social networks and metadata.

- [mosint](https://github.com/alpkeskin/mosint) â€” a utility for collecting information about emails/accounts/domains.

> **Tip:** Place your custom scripts in `tools/my-osint-scripts/` and add links to them in this file:
> ```markdown
> - [My scripts (examples)](./my-osint-scripts/)
> ```

